# BSI WID provider profile for SecurityPortal
# ============================================================================
# This file is a ready-to-use env profile for testing against the real BSI
# CERT-Bund WID (Warn- und Informationsdienst) CSAF Trusted Provider at
# https://wid.cert-bund.de.
#
# Usage:
#   docker compose --env-file docker/.env.wid.example up
#
# Copy and adjust for production; never commit a real .env with secrets.
# ============================================================================

# --- CSAF Trusted Provider ingestion ---
#
# Direct PMD URL form: when SECURITYPORTAL_PROVIDER_URL starts with "https://",
# the gocsaf ProviderMetadataLoader.Load() short-circuits at line 160-162 of
# providermetaloader.go and fetches the JSON directly from this URL, bypassing
# the well-known/.security.txt/DNS discovery steps entirely.  No code change to
# pkg/ingest/provider.go is required — config only (spec §16.6).
SECURITYPORTAL_PROVIDER_URL=https://wid.cert-bund.de/.well-known/csaf/provider-metadata.json

# TLP labels that are publishable.  The BSI WID corpus is predominantly
# TLP:WHITE (public) advisories; UNLABELED covers the small number of
# documents that carry no explicit TLP label.
SECURITYPORTAL_PUBLISHABLE_TLP=WHITE,UNLABELED

# Poll interval.  The BSI WID corpus is large (thousands of mostly-German
# TLP:WHITE advisories) and the ingestion pipeline performs a full pull on
# every poll cycle (OQ-6 — no incremental delta yet).  6 h avoids hammering
# the provider while keeping the portal reasonably current.  Shorten for
# initial testing once the database has been seeded; restore for steady-state.
SECURITYPORTAL_POLL_INTERVAL=6h

# --- PostgreSQL ---
# Replace with real credentials before deploying.  These placeholders are
# for local development only; never commit a .env with real passwords.
POSTGRES_USER=securityportal
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=changeme
POSTGRES_DB=securityportal
# SECURITYPORTAL_DATABASE_DSN is auto-derived from the POSTGRES_* vars above
# by docker-compose.yml (postgres://${POSTGRES_USER}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@db:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}?sslmode=disable).
# You only need to set it explicitly when overriding the default — e.g. an
# external (non-bundled) DB host, or a password containing URL-reserved
# characters that require percent-encoding (RFC 3986 §2.1).
# SECURITYPORTAL_DATABASE_DSN=postgres://securityportal:changeme@db:5432/securityportal?sslmode=disable

# --- Read-only HTTP API ---
# Same-origin via Caddy: CORS headers are not needed (ADR-0011).
SECURITYPORTAL_CORS_ORIGINS=
SECURITYPORTAL_QUERY_TIMEOUT=5s

# --- SSR / API base split (ADR-0011 / task 33) ---
SECURITYPORTAL_API_INTERNAL_URL=http://api:8081

# --- Branding (optional) — mirror of Helm values.yaml branding knobs ---
# All vars are optional; unset (or empty) keeps the application's built-in
# default.  The web service reads them at SSR time via runtime-config.ts:
# any empty or whitespace-only value is treated as "unset" (spec §16.2).
#
# SP_BRANDING_DIR=./branding
# SECURITYPORTAL_BRAND_NAME=
# SECURITYPORTAL_BRAND_SUBTITLE=
# SECURITYPORTAL_THEME_PRIMARY=
# SECURITYPORTAL_THEME_PRIMARY_FG=
# SECURITYPORTAL_THEME_ACCENT=
# SECURITYPORTAL_LOGO_PATH=

# --- Caddy reverse proxy (ADR-0011) ---
# Set SP_SITE_ADDRESS to the public FQDN when using ACME (MODE 2).
SP_SITE_ADDRESS=localhost
# SP_ACME_EMAIL=ops@example.com

# Rate limiting — 60 req/min per source IP is the default; lower for testing.
SP_RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=60
SP_RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=1m

# --- Verify pipeline ---
# The ingestion worker validates every downloaded advisory against its
# accompanying .sha256 / .sha512 hash files and, when present, the PGP
# signature (.asc) in the ROLIE feed.  The BSI WID provider publishes
# advisories signed with its own PGP key, so this profile exercises the full
# hash-and-PGP verify pipeline against real keys.  No extra configuration is
# required; the gocsaf library fetches the public key URLs listed in the
# provider-metadata.json automatically.
#
# NOTE: live integration tests against this provider must be tagged as
# network tests and excluded from the default `go test` run (spec §16.6).
